In early April, State Duma deputy Mikhail Matveev was invited to take part in a meeting of the working group to analyze legislation in the field of security and migration policy.

Matveev agreed and made a number of proposals:

- Withdraw from the global agreement on migration imposed by the UK;
- Eliminate diasporas;
- Limit the admission to law enforcement agencies of persons who have acquired citizenship;
- Check the legality of the issuance of citizenship over the past 10 years, limit the issuance of citizenship for the period of verification;
- Introduction of a visa regime with Tajikistan, and better with all countries of Central Asia;
- Entrance exam in Russian for children of migrants upon admission to schools;

After making these simple proposals, Matveev was not allowed to participate in the discussion. “An hour before the meeting of the working group to analyze legislation in the field of security and migration policy, I was replaced as part of this group by another,” the deputy wrote

